(A. Architecture Overview) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 391.75 Tm
(fun.lol is implemented as a lightweight single-page web application with a Node.js backend. The frontend is delivered from static) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 378.25 Tm
(files and switches between an authenticated dashboard, a bio/profile editor, public profile pages, games, friends, tribes, and tribe) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 364.75 Tm
(chats. The backend exposes JSON API routes for authentication, profile publishing, media delivery, friends, tribes, tribe chat, and) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 351.25 Tm
(the server-backed Snake score.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 334.75 Tm
(Confirmed implementation:) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 318.25 Tm
(- Frontend files: `index.html`, `script.js`, and `styles.css`.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 304.75 Tm
(- Backend entry point: `server.js`, using Node's built-in `http` module rather than Express or another framework.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 291.25 Tm
(- Static routing: `/` serves `index.html`; `/u/:handle` also serves `index.html` so the client can load a public profile by handle.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 277.75 Tm
(- API routing: `/api/...` routes are handled directly in `server.js`.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 264.25 Tm
(- Local persistence fallback: `data/users.json` and `data/profiles.json`.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 250.75 Tm
(- Optional Supabase persistence: enabled when `SUPABASE_URL` and `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` are present.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 237.25 Tm
(- Supabase tables currently defined in `supabase-schema.sql`: `app_users`, `app_sessions`, and `app_profiles`.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 223.75 Tm
(- Supabase Storage bucket used by the server when configured: `profile-media`.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 210.25 Tm
(- Public discovery support: `/robots.txt` and `/sitemap.xml`.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 196.75 Tm
(Storage model:) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 180.25 Tm
(- In local mode, users and sessions are stored in `data/users.json`; profiles and most social features are stored in) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 166.75 Tm
(`data/profiles.json`.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 153.25 Tm
(- In Supabase mode, users are stored in `app_users`, sessions in `app_sessions`, and profile data in `app_profiles.data` as JSONB.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 139.75 Tm
(- Friends, friend requests, tribes, tribe invites, join requests, tribe messages, profile settings, media references, social links,) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 126.25 Tm
(and most profile customization data are logical entities currently nested inside profile JSON.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 112.75 Tm
(- Media files are stored as data URLs in profile JSON when Supabase is not configured. When Supabase is configured, uploaded avatar,) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 99.25 Tm
(background, and music files are moved into Supabase Storage and referenced by path.) Tj
